article.description: — Jaren Holmes had 19 points and 11 rebounds to carry Saint Bonaventure to a 69-58 win over Davidson on Sunday, the Bonnies’ seventh consecutive home victory.
article.headline: Holmes leads Saint Bonaventure over Davidson 69-58
article.linkText: Holmes leads Saint Bonaventure over Davidson 69-58
article.story: ST. BONAVENTURE, N.Y. -- — Jaren Holmes had 19 points and 11 rebounds to carry Saint Bonaventure to a 69-58 win over Davidson on Sunday, the Bonnies’ seventh consecutive home victory. Holmes made 5 of 7 3-pointers. Kyle Lofton had 18 points and six assists for Saint Bonaventure (11-3, 9-3 Atlantic 10 Conference). Jalen Adaway added six rebounds. Davidson scored 26 first-half points, a season low for the team. Hyunjung Lee and Kellan Grady scored 18 points apiece for the Wildcats (11-6, 6-3), whose five-game win streak came to an end. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
